	abstract = {Deep models are learned from data and so both predictions and inferences from these models can be highly sensitive to data included and excluded from analysis. We survey approaches to improve deep learning prediction through undersampling, oversampling, negative sampling, data augmentation and transfer learning to maximize the ability of deep models to discriminate. We also explore the range of methods for building samples that allow us to make credible inferences about underlying populations of phenomena our data are intended to represent, and for building bounds that allow us to state those with confidence. Finally, we explore how to model the correctness of human annotations and annotators when humans are in the loop to maximize the signal and minimize the noise from their assessments.},
