	abstract = {Background: Many instances of coordination problems in social networks can be characterized by the well-known graph coloring game—a task in which agents are incentivized to choose an attribute, represented by a color, to be different from linked neighbors. Past work on this topic, however, is limited to static networks of speciﬁc topologies of interest.
